{"word":"G4121 - πλεονάζω - pleonázō - pleh-on-ad'-zo - Abound","slug":"G4121","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">πλεονάζω</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Transliteration: </strong>pleonázō"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Phonetic: </strong>pleh-on-ad'-zo"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Short Definition: </strong>Abound"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b>&#x03C0;&#x03BB;&#x03B5;&#x03BF;&#x03BD;&#x03B1;&#x0301;&#x03B6;&#x03C9; - pleonazo&#x0304;</b> - <i>pleh-on-ad'-zo</i><p/>From <a href=\"#/G4119\">G4119</a>; to <i>do</i>, <i>make</i> or <i>be more</i>, that is, <i>increase</i> (transitively or intransitively); by extension to <i>superabound:</i> - abound, abundant, make to increase, have over."},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Cognate:</strong> <a href=\"#/G4122\">G4122</a>, <a href=\"#/G4123\">G4123</a>"}]}